-- Turkey Stocks: Akfen, Emlak, Finansbank, TAV, Turk Traktor Move
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2011-12-16T16:22:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-16/turkey-stocks-akfen-emlak-finansbank-tav-turk-traktor-move.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 0.4 percent to 51,665.78 at the 5:30 p.m. close in
Istanbul, increasing this week’s decline to 4 percent.  The following stocks were active on the Turkish stock
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Akfen Holding AS (AKFEN)  , a Turkish group with interests
in construction, energy, tourism and port operations, rose for a
second day, climbing 2.3 percent to 8 liras. Six companies,
including Aeroports de Paris, are interested in buying shares in
 TAV Havalimanlari Holding AS (TAVHL)  , Turkey’s biggest
airport operator whose owners Akfen and Tepe Insaat Sanayi AS
hired Credit Suisse Group AG in September for a possible stake
sale, Vatan newspaper reported, without citing anyone.  TAV Havalimanlari jumped 4.7 percent to 8.02 liras.  Finansbank AS  (FINBN TI), owned by National Bank of Greece
SA, surged 13 percent to 4.58 liras, the highest level since
Oct. 28, after the Macedonian Information Agency said NBG will
sell a stake.  Turk Traktor & Ziraat Makineleri AS (TTRAK)  , a Turkish
tractor maker, jumped 2.2 percent to 31.90 liras, the highest
level in more than a month. The bourse will add Turk Traktor to
the index of the top 30 companies from Jan. 1, as part of
quarterly changes in the indexes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
